## Understanding the Stages

### Stage 1: Original Input
All messages flow to a single destination regardless of content, severity, region, or type.

### Stage 2: Severity-Based Routing
Critical and warning messages are routed to appropriate alerting systems (PagerDuty, Slack) while informational messages go to searchable storage (Elasticsearch).

### Stage 3: Geographic Routing
Regional routing enforces data residency requirements - EU data stays in EU systems for GDPR compliance, while US data routes to regional clusters for performance.

### Stage 4: Event Type Routing
Different event types (authentication, payments, telemetry, analytics) are routed to specialized processing systems optimized for each data type.

### Stage 5: Priority Queue Routing
Messages are routed to different priority queues based on user tier and urgency, ensuring premium users and critical events get expedited processing.

