## Common Questions

### Why do conditions need to be ordered from specific to general?
Switch outputs evaluate conditions in order and use the first match. If general conditions come first, specific conditions will never be reached. For example, checking `region == "eu-west"` before `region == "eu-west" && severity == "CRITICAL"` ensures the specific case is handled.

### What happens if no conditions match?
Without a default case (no condition), unmatched messages cause errors. Always include a final case with no `check` property to handle unexpected data gracefully.

### How do I test routing logic?
Send test messages with different field values and verify they reach the expected destinations. Use pipeline metrics to monitor routing distribution and identify unhandled cases.

